article.headline: Pierce's 20 lead Presbyterian past Youngstown State 67-42
article.description: — Jonah Pierce had 20 points in Presbyterian's 67-42 win against Youngstown State on Friday night.
article.linkText: Pierce's 20 lead Presbyterian past Youngstown State 67-42
article.story: HUNTSVILLE, Texas -- — Jonah Pierce had 20 points in Presbyterian's 67-42 win against Youngstown State on Friday night. Pierce added nine rebounds for the Blue Hose (4-3). Kory Mincy scored 12 points, shooting 5 for 11, including 2 for 5 from beyond the arc. Kobe Stewart had 11 points and finished 4 of 9 from the field. The Penguins (2-3) were led by Ty Harper, who posted 12 points. EJ Farmer added 10 points and three steals for Youngstown State. Nico Galette also had five points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
